			"title": "Bada Haridas Prabhu&#039;s Bhajans",
			"date": "Sun, Dec 03, 2017",
			"author": "Niranjana Swami",
			"body": "<p>\r\n\tLast night I was chanting bhajans with the devotees assembled in the Towaco community both before and after Dhirasanta Maharaja's wonderful talk from Bhagavad-gita about the importance of controlling the mind.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\tWhen devotees were asking me to chant certain bhajans, most of which I had learned from Bada Haridas Prabhu, I felt I should give credit where credit is due.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\tBefore chanting the next bhajan, I decided to ask permission to tell a short story about how I came to learn bhajans from Bada Haridas Prabhu.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\tAfter telling my story, which I won't repeat here due to time limits, I told everyone that I was holding on to many recordings of my first visit with Bada Haridas Prabhu in the late 1990's when I spent several evenings together with him and Panca Tattva dasa (also from Alachua) just chanting different bhajans with him and recording them for the purpose of learning them from him.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\tIt was during those recordings, that I realized that the Alachua community was in possession of a very valuable jewel which needed to be shared with the rest of the world. So I invited Bada Haridas Prabhu to come to Ukraine.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\tThe rest is history… again, another story too long to repeat here.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\tI promised the devotees attending the Towaco program that I would make the bhajans Panca Tattva dasa recorded for me during those evenings in Alachua available for everyone if they wished to download them.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\tI told everyone that I had approximately sixty recordings, which is true, but after looking at the files I realized that a good part of those recordings were done at a time other than when I was personally with Bada Haridas Prabhu. Before making all those additional recordings available, therefore, I should first check with Bada Haridas Prabhu and ask him if it's OK to release them.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\tMeanwhile, I will post 16 of those recordings. These are the only ones I can find right now from the ones we chanted together in Alachua in the late 90's. Bada Haridas Prabhu was leading, I was drinking the nectar of his association and was also playing the mrdanga because there were only three of us present. Panca Tattva dasa was playing kartals.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\tYou can download the files by clicking <a href=\"https://drive.google.com/a/niranjanaswami.org/file/d/1QHG51keDv3Hu9d2VgcZB6hjA1fsNAnMw/view?usp=sharing\">HERE</a>.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\tHare Krishna\r\n</p>\r\n",
